  "text": "Repeated electrical stimulation of the cat auditory cortex resulted in a progression in electrographic activity (with increases in spike amplitude, frequency and complexity) and the corresponding seizure severity in most animals. The baseline afterdischarge thresholds (ADT) ranged from 100 to 800 µA (mean of 370 µA). Figure 2 illustrates the increase in AD duration with repeated stimulation from the initial stimulation ( Fig. 2A) to the 20th stimulation session (Fig. 2C ) for a representative individual animal. The increase in mean AD duration (for all kindling animals) and corresponding average seizure severity are summarized in Figure 2B . The behavioral manifestations of the seizure activity became progressively more severe with the repeated occurrence of AD and were classified into stages according to [CITATION_1] . We report the failure of kindling progression in approximately one-third of the cats, consistent with findings in the rat auditory cortex [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
